title.narrative: Myanmar National Community Driven Development Project

description.narrative: The development objective is to enable poor rural communities to benefit from improved access to and use of basic infrastructure and services through a people-centered approach and to enhance the government’s capacity to respond promptly and effectively to an eligible crisis or emergency.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement : ARTICLE IV | Description : The Co-financing Deadline for the effectiveness of the Co-financing Agreement isSeptember 30, 2016

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2-Section II.A.1. | Description :Preparation of quarterly Project Reports, following adoption ofProject Operations Manual, due within 45 days after the end of the period covered. | Due Date :15-Nov-2014

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2-Section II.A.3 | Description :Conduct of mid-term progress review, under terms of referencesatisfactory to the Association, and adoption of any resultant measures for the effective implementation of the Project in formsatisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :30-Apr-2015

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2-Section II.B.4 | Description :Appointment of the independent auditors with qualifications, experienceand terms of reference satisfactory to the Association | Due Date :11-Apr-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2-Section II.B.5 | Description :Installation of an accounting and financial management software at theDepartment of Rural Development, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association | Due Date :11-Jul-2013
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2-Section IV.B.1(b) | Description :Preparation and adoption of a Project Operations Manual in form andsubstance satisfactory to the Association | Due Date :30-Sep-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2-Section IV.B.1(c) | Description :Declaration of an Eligible Crisis or Emergency, and the Associationhas agreed with such determination; preparation and disclosure,in form and substance satisfactory to the Association, of allsafeguards instruments required and implementation of any actions which are required to be taken under said instruments;establishment of adequate implementation arrangements, satisfactory to the Association | Due Date :31-Jan-2019

Financing Agreement: Schedule 2, Section II A.2.I Description: Prepare and furnish to the Association a mid-term report, in suchdetail as the Association shall reasonably request, documenting progress achieved in the carrying out of the Project during theperiod preceding the date of such report, taking into account the monitoring and evaluation activities performed pursuant toparagraph 1 of Section II.A of Finance Agreement.
